Join us today as we remember and honour two of our fallen brothers Cyril Fyfe and Kevin Olson. The tragedy occurred on March 17, 2005 when fire fighters responded to a fire at a hardware store. Fyfe and Olson were trapped under a roof that collapsed during the fire.Olson, who was 24 and on the job just 10 days, died that day. Fyfe, 41, was in a coma for four days before being taken off life support. He had been a Yellowknife fire fighter for 18 years. … See more

Today we acknowledge two City of Yellowknife firefighters, Lieutenant Cyril Fyfe and Firefighter Kevin Olson, who lost their lives while serving our community on March 17, 2005. The flags at City Hall and the Fire Hall are flying at half-mast today in their memory and to honour their lives and bravery.We respect and value the work of all those who put their safety at risk to keep our community safe.

Yellowknife RCMP overnight update – August 18th, 2023On August 18th, 2023, at 4:01 a.m. the Yellowknife RMCP received a call reporting a fire on the Deh Cho Boulevard. RCMP officers immediately attended after confirming that Yellowknife Fire had been dispatched.
